<HEADLINE>
<P>
STATISTICS ON SMOKING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
More cities are just saying "no smoking." I am a smoker. 
</P>
<P>
But how can you ban something that is not illegal. The anti-smokers have rights 
I agree, but I have a right, too. It is called freedom of choice. I am very 
considerate about smoking. If someone in the room doesn't smoke, I ask if it is 
OK. But if they are rude, like most of the anti-smokers, so am I. Plus, I don't 
see how secondhand smoke is so bad because there are a lot of other things such 
as smog that are worse. 
</P>
<P>
GREG NICHOLS 
</P>
<P>
Anaheim 
