<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chemical giant W. R. Grace &amp; Co. has selected Vice Chairman J. P. Bolduc as 
president and chief operating officer. 
</P>
<P>
Bolduc, 51, will succeed Charles H. Erhart Jr., 65, who is retiring as 
president but will continue as a director. Erhart had been president for a 
little more than a year. The post of chief operating officer has been vacant 
since 1986. The move appears to put Bolduc in line to succeed Chairman and CEO 
J. Peter Grace should the 77-year-old chairman decide to step down. 
</P>
</TEXT>
