<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: STABBING VICTIM'S CONDITION IMPROVES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PSYCHE PASCUAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The condition of a Santa Paula man who was stabbed 18 times has improved from 
critical to guarded, a Ventura County Medical Center nursing supervisor said 
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Avelino Morales, 28, was admitted to the hospital late Friday after the knife 
attack. 
</P>
<P>
But the identity of the assailants who repeatedly knifed Morales remains a 
mystery, Santa Paula Police Cmdr. Bob Gonzalez said. 
</P>
<P>
Morales was walking with a friend at 10:29 p.m. Friday in the 1200 block of 
East Ventura Street when they were approached by two men in their mid-20s. 
</P>
<P>
Morales was stabbed in the chest, back and both legs. The two attackers fled on 
foot, Gonzalez said. 
</P>
<P>
Police are not revealing the name of Morales' friend out of concern that he may 
be attacked in retaliation for his testimony, Gonzalez said. 
</P>
<P>
Officers have been unable to determine whether a gang was involved in the 
stabbing because Morales' friend could not identify the attackers by name, 
Gonzalez said. 
</P>
<P>
Police plan to interview Morales when he is released from the hospital, 
Gonzalez said. PSYCHE PASCUAL 
</P>
</TEXT>
