<P>
DIGEST /LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: PALMDALE JUDGE PICKED FOR APPELLATE COURT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gov. George Deukmejian will nominate a Palmdale judge to serve as associate 
justice of the 2nd Appellate District, Division 5, the governor's office 
announced Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Judge Margaret M. Grignon, 39, the first and only woman Superior Court judge in 
the Antelope Valley, will be named to replace Justice Paul Turner. 
</P>
<P>
Turner has been nominated to be presiding justice of the division. 
</P>
<P>
Deukmejian appointed Grignon to the Antelope Valley Municipal Court in 1984 and 
to the Los Angeles County Superior Court in 1987. 
</P>
<P>
Grignon, her husband and two children have lived in the Antelope Valley for 
seven years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
