<TEXT>
<P>
An earthquake with a magnitude of 4.5 sharply jolted the northern Iranian town 
of Rudbaon on Monday, more than month after a quake killed 40,000 people in the 
region. 
</P>
<P>
There was no immediate report of damage or injuries. 
</P>
