<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: CAR PLUNGES OFF FREEWAY ONTO STREET, 
KILLING DRIVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A car plunged off the Harbor Freeway onto a city street Monday, killing the 
driver, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The vehicle went off the northbound Harbor Freeway onto Grand Avenue near 69th 
Street in South Los Angeles about 5 p.m. California Highway Patrol spokesman 
Vince Zambrano said. 
</P>
<P>
A woman was killed in the accident, Zambrano said. Additional details were not 
immediately available. The outside lane of the freeway was closed for less than 
an hour after the accident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
