<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: TRANSAMERICA INSURANCE GROUP PROFIT FALLS 27% IN QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Transamerica Insurance Group in Woodland Hills, citing lower investment gains, 
said its second-quarter profit fell 27% from a year earlier, despite a 13% 
increase in revenue. 
</P>
<P>
In the quarter that ended June 30, Transamerica Insurance earned $20 million, 
down from $27.5 million, while its revenue climbed to $526.1 million from 
$465.4 million. 
</P>
<P>
The earnings decline reflected a 54% drop in the company's gains from 
investment transactions, to $4.14 million from $8.95 million. 
</P>
<P>
For the first half of 1990, Transamerica Insurance's net income fell 14% to 
$33.6 million from $39.2 million a year earlier, and its six-month revenue rose 
10% to $1.05 billion from $931.5 million. 
</P>
<P>
The company is the property/casualty insurance unit of Transamerica Corp., a 
financial services concern based in San Francisco. 
</P>
</TEXT>
