<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: RADIO STATION KBET-AM FILES FOR REORGANIZATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KBET, the only radio station in the Santa Clarita Valley, filed for 
reorganization under Chapter 11 of the federal bankruptcy laws. 
</P>
<P>
The July 23 filing "will allow us to catch our breath and reposition the debts" 
of the 1,000-watt station on 1220 AM, said Carl Goldman, a consultant brought 
in to oversee the station's restructuring. 
</P>
<P>
Under Chapter 11, a company is protected from creditors' lawsuits while it 
works out a strategy to pay its bills. 
</P>
<P>
The station listed assets of $275,000 and debts of $2.3 million. 
</P>
<P>
KBET, owned by Canyon Broadcasters Inc. in Canyon Country, has struggled under 
financial and legal problems since it debuted in mid-1989. Last month, it 
indefinitely laid off several on-air personalities and switched to a format of 
playing only Beatles songs. The station switched formats again last week and 
now plays "oldies" music. 
</P>
<P>
Canyon Broadcasters is attempting to sell the station, which plans to retain 
its "oldies" format at least until it is sold, Goldman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
