<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: INCOMNET'S EARNINGS UP 35% IN 2ND QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Incomnet Inc. of Westlake Village said it earned $139,237 in the second quarter 
that ended June 30, up 35% from $103,454 in net income a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
Revenues rose 86% to $756,916 from $407,638. 
</P>
<P>
The company, which runs a computerized auto parts trading network, said that in 
the six months ending in June earnings fell 39% to $189,926 from $311,060 in 
the same period in 1989. Revenues increased 89% to $1.54 million from $816,325. 
</P>
<P>
The company said the decline in earnings in the six-month period was due to 
securities gains of $442,206 in 1989's first half. Otherwise, it said, results 
improved because of growth in its computerized trading network and new software 
division. 
</P>
