<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: 3-D SYSTEMS RECORDS $129,163 QUARTERLY PROFIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
3-D Systems Inc., a Canadian company whose primary unit is a Valencia operation 
with the same name, reported a second-quarter profit of $129,163, compared with 
a loss of $969,262 a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
3-D makes a machine that uses chemicals, a laser and a computer to rapidly 
build models of parts, consumer packages and other items that are used as 
prototypes by manufacturers. 
</P>
<P>
The company only recently began full-scale shipments of its machines, which has 
improved its sales and earnings. 
</P>
<P>
In the quarter that ended June 30, 3-D's sales jumped to $7.07 million from 
$3.73 million a year earlier. For the first half of this year, the company 
earned $529,784 on sales of $14.3 million. In the first six months of 1989, 3-D 
lost $2.74 million on sales of $5.31 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
