<HEADLINE>
<P>
BABY GIRL'S BODY FOUND IN TRASH; WOMAN ARRESTED; 
</P>
<P>
CRIME: A SANTA ANA 19-YEAR-OLD WAS BOOKED ON SUSPICION OF MURDER AFTER THE 
INFANT'S BODY WAS RECOVERED FROM THE BOTTOM OF A DUMPSTER. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATT LAIT and JIM CARLTON, TIMES STAFF WRITERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANAHEIM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Santa Ana woman was arrested on suspicion of murder Monday after the body of 
a baby girl believed to be hers was found in a Dumpster, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Alejandra Baena, 19, was booked into the Anaheim City Jail after police 
recovered the baby girl's body from a Dumpster behind an apartment complex in 
the 800 block of South Anaheim Boulevard about 5:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
Officials at the scene estimated that the baby had been dead for several days. 
</P>
<P>
Residents in the nearby apartments said there had been an odor since Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
An autopsy was scheduled for today. 
</P>
<P>
Lt. Ray Welch said the age of the baby was not immediately known. He said 
police were first alerted by an anonymous call at 1:30 p.m. Monday that there 
was a dead baby "in a container" near the apartment complex. At the direction 
of another witness, officers searched a large bin used for commercial waste, 
Welch said. 
</P>
<P>
Welch said officers enlisted the help of a local sanitation crew to empty the 
Dumpster. After sifting through debris for two hours, Welch said, the body was 
discovered at the bottom of the Dumpster. 
</P>
<P>
Anaheim homicide detectives tracked down Baena after questioning residents in 
the vicinity, Welch said. 
</P>
<P>
At the apartment complex, residents said Baena was a gentle-natured woman who 
baby-sat for Maria Candidad Romero's three children. 
</P>
<P>
Romero said that she did not know Baena had been pregnant. 
</P>
<P>
"She hid it," Romero said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
