</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Douglas to Launch Satellite: McDonnell Douglas Space Systems Co. said it plans 
to launch a second satellite for British Satellite Broadcasting Ltd. on Aug. 15 
at 3:48 p.m. from Cape Canaveral, Fla. 
</P>
<P>
The satellite, designed and built by Hughes Aircraft Co., will join another 
satellite 20,173 miles above Earth to provide the United Kingdom with more than 
twice its present television broadcast capability. 
</P>
<P>
The satellite will be carried aboard a Delta II rocket and will be the fifth 
commercial satellite to be launched by McDonnell Douglas. The company has 
contracts to launch seven more commercial satellites. 
</P>
</TEXT>
