<TEXT>
<P>
Not Part of the Deal: There's one business unit associated with Newport 
Beach-based Ford Aerospace, the defense and communications subsidiary of Ford 
Motor Co., that was not included in the $715-million cash purchase by New 
York-based Loral Corp. 
</P>
<P>
Ford Microelectronics Inc., which employs about 200 people in Colorado Springs, 
Colo., was not part of the deal, said Ford spokesman Tom Rhoades. The 
subsidiary, which makes semiconductors, was never formally part of Ford 
Aerospace and it will be retained by the parent company, Rhoades said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
