<P>
DOG BREATH? HARRODS HAS THE ANSWER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Deutsche Presse Agentur 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONDON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Harrods, London's luxury department store, today presented a new toothpaste for 
dogs that fights tooth decay and promises to give pets fresh breath. 
</P>
<P>
"Britain has nearly 7 million dogs, and their life expectancy is increasing. 
</P>
<P>
But often they have decaying teeth and gums, and their breath smells foul 
because they are fed on dog food that is soft," said Dr. Roger Mugford, an 
animal behaviorist. 
</P>
<P>
Mugford told reporters at the presentation of the new Petrodex toothpaste that 
he had tried the product out himself on a long-haired Irish setter and a 
short-legged Welsh corgi. "They loved the paste since it tastes malty," he 
said. 
</P>
<P>
But he conceded that he would not venture to try to brush just any dog's teeth, 
saying: "I would think about it with a Rottweiler" -- a breed known for its 
sharp teeth. 
</P>
