<P>
FOX CHANGES ITS 'ROBIN HOOD' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FROM TIMES WIRE SERVICES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hollywood's Robin Hood Derby took a new turn Monday when 20th Century Fox 
announced plans to make "The Adventures of Robin Hood" as a three-hour 
made-for-TV movie instead of a feature film. 
</P>
<P>
The studio suspended the project when it was learned that Morgan Creek 
Productions had signed Kevin Costner to "Prince of Thieves," a $40-million 
Robin Hood saga to be distributed sometime next year by Warner Bros. 
</P>
<P>
Fox's TV movie, which is likely to air here before "Prince of Thieves" is 
released, will be distributed theatrically abroad. 
</P>
</TEXT>
