SHORT TAKES; 
</P>
<P>
JANET JACKSON DELAYS SHOWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FROM TIMES WIRE SERVICES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ST. LOUIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Singer Janet Jackson postponed two concerts this week in Detroit after passing 
out backstage in the middle of a St. Louis show. 
</P>
<P>
Jackson, 24, collapsed Sunday after singing three songs. 
</P>
<P>
She was taken to a hospital, treated for an acute viral infection and released, 
Kathleen Heinz, a spokeswoman for the St. Louis Arena, said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
A doctor recommended Jackson not perform for at least four or five days, Heinz 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Jackson, the sister of Michael Jackson, has suffered from exhaustion during her 
"Rhythm Nation" tour and had come down with a fever and an ear infection that 
caused dizziness the day before she passed out, Heinz said. 
</P>
<P>
The Detroit concerts had been scheduled for today and Wednesday but were moved 
to Aug. 22 and 23. 
</P>
</TEXT>
